{
  "answer": "**Manusmṛti, Chapter 3.**\n\nThe eight forms of marriage (*vivāha*) are enumerated together in verses 3.20–21 (paragraphs [p-36d967](https://falsafa.corpus/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/03/translation/#p-36d967) and [p-b07c61](https://falsafa.corpus/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/03/translation/#p-b07c61)):\n\n> Now learn in summary these eight forms of marriage for women, for the four *varnas*, which are beneficial and harmful in this world and the next. // Mn_3.20 //[^1]  \n>   \n> The `Brāhma`, the `Daiva`, and also the `Ārṣa`; the `Prājāpatya` and the `Āsura`; the `Gāndharva` and the `Rākṣasa`; and the eighth and lowest, the `Paiśāca`. // Mn_3.21 //[^1]\n\nThese match the query details: the *Gāndharva* is \"the voluntary union of a maiden and her lover... which springs from desire\" (3.32, [p-beb0f2](https://falsafa.corpus/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/03/translation/#p-beb0f2));[^2] the *Rākṣasa* involves \"forcible abduction... after her kinsmen have been slain\" (3.33, [p-2f28cf](https://falsafa.corpus/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/03/translation/#p-2f28cf));[^3] and the *Paiśāca* is a \"clandestine approach to a... sleeping [or] intoxicated girl... the eighth and most wicked\" (3.34, [p-ca03b2](https://falsafa.corpus/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/03/translation/#p-ca03b2)).[^4]\n\n[^1]: Manusmṛti, *Chapter 3*, [paragraphs p-36d967–p-b07c61](https://falsafa.corpus/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/03/translation/#p-36d967).\n[^2]: Manusmṛti, *Chapter 3*, [paragraph p-beb0f2](https://falsafa.corpus/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/03/translation/#p-beb0f2).\n[^3]: Manusmṛti, *Chapter 3*, [paragraph p-2f28cf](https://falsafa.corpus/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/03/translation/#p-2f28cf).\n[^4]: Manusmṛti, *Chapter 3*, [paragraph p-ca03b2](https://falsafa.corpus/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/03/translation/#p-ca03b2).",
